**The standard is a clock, not a stopwatch. The stopwatch measured the sprint that ended at deployment. The clock measures the rhythm that runs from deployment until the system is retired. The organization that put the stopwatch down at deployment, declared the program a success and moved on, has not started the clock. The clock starts whether the organization starts it or not. The cadence runs. The cadence is either being kept or not. The deployment record is either present or not. The named human is either on the signature or not. The inquiry will arrive. The inquiry will ask what time it was. The organization that has been keeping a clock will have an answer. The organization that has been watching a stopwatch will discover, in the moment of being asked, that the instrument it was using was the wrong one, and that the interval the instrument measured ended a long time ago.**

