## How to Use This Template

You cannot govern what you have not named. The Agent Registry is the centralized inventory of every AI system the organization has deployed, is piloting or has authorized for development, including AI features embedded in commercial software, AI systems deployed by individual business units without central IT involvement and AI agents operating as components of larger orchestrated systems. The structural response to shadow AI is not awareness training. It is registration as a precondition for use.

Each entry contains the information needed to govern the system: purpose and intended use; EU AI Act actor designation and risk classification; internal impact classification; named system owner; oversight mode; trust boundary specification by reference; evidence retention policy; and date of last governance review. The Registry is not a one-time document. It is a living record. A system that was registered as minimal risk and has since been deployed in a regulated sector context is no longer a minimal risk system regardless of what the Registry says; the mechanism owner who fails to update the Registry has created a governance gap through which the system operates outside the controls that would apply if its actual deployment context were known.

For each entry: complete all fields. Do not leave fields blank. Where a field is not applicable, state the basis for non-applicability. The Registry is reviewed for completeness by a named mechanism owner at defined intervals (quarterly is the minimum default; faster cadence required for high-impact systems and for organizations in active scaling). New entries require approval at the level appropriate to the system’s impact classification before the system reaches production.

This template is synchronized with Appendix I Section 0 (Pre-Audit Scoping: Inventory and Actor Classification). Where an audit checklist question can be answered by reference to a Registry field, cross-reference rather than restate; the Registry is the system of record for system inventory.

