## How to Use This Template

This template operationalizes EU AI Act Art. 27, which requires deployers meeting the applicability conditions to conduct a Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment before first use of a high-risk AI system. The six statutory elements of Art. 27(1) are distributed across Sections A through H. Section D is the core rights-impact assessment; all other sections are context, evidence, mitigation and governance framing for Section D.

This template is pre-aligned with the model card minimums in Part 6.4 of the current AI GRC Master Reference. Fields in Sections B that correspond to model card fields are marked with their alignment relationship: cross-reference only (no restatement), restate with rights-impact framing (restatement required), or supplement (deployment-specific additions required). The full alignment matrix is at Appendix F-1.

Where GDPR Art. 35 also requires a Data Protection Impact Assessment, this template is designed to function as the FRIA component of a coordinated FRIA-DPIA. Section G5 records the coordination. The FRIA does not substitute for the DPIA; both sets of statutory elements must be satisfied.

For each section: complete all fields. Do not leave fields blank. Where a field is not applicable, state the basis for non-applicability. Market surveillance authorities may review this document; the standard is a completed, reasoned assessment, not a checklist of procedural acknowledgments.

Field color coding in Section D: mandatory rights assessment fields are shaded. Non-shaded rights must be assessed where potentially relevant to the deployment context; if not relevant, record that determination with brief rationale rather than leaving the row blank.

